{"id":2786,"date":"2024-05-10T11:25:32","date_gmt":"2024-05-10T11:25:32","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/?p=2786"},"modified":"2024-05-10T11:25:32","modified_gmt":"2024-05-10T11:25:32","slug":"can-commerce-student-do-data-analytics","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/can-commerce-student-do-data-analytics\/","title":{"rendered":"Can Commerce Student Do Data Analytics?"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Commerce students can pursue a career in data analytics. Data analytics is a field that involves the examination, cleansing, transformation, and interpretation of data to discover valuable insights and support decision-making. While a background in computer science or mathematics can be advantageous, it&#8217;s not a strict requirement for a career in data analytics. Here&#8217;s why commerce students can excel in this field:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Analytical Skills<\/strong>: Commerce students often possess strong analytical skills, which are crucial for data analytics. They are used to working with financial data and performing various types of analysis.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Statistical Knowledge<\/strong>: Many commerce programs include statistics courses, which provide a foundation for understanding and working with data.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Business Acumen<\/strong>: Commerce students often have a good understanding of business processes and operations, making them well-suited for data analytics roles in business and finance.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tools and Software<\/strong>: Data analytics often involves using software tools like Excel, SQL, and data visualization tools. Commerce students may already be familiar with these tools from their coursework.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Additional Training<\/strong>: If a commerce student is interested in data analytics, they can pursue additional training in data analysis and data science through online courses, workshops, or more formal education programs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Soft Skills<\/strong>: Communication, problem-solving, and critical thinking skills are essential in data analytics. Commerce students often develop these skills through their coursework.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s important for commerce students interested in data analytics to learn programming languages like Python and R, as these are commonly used in the field. They should also gain proficiency in data visualization and statistical analysis techniques. Building a portfolio of data analysis projects can help demonstrate their skills to potential employers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In summary, while a background in computer science or mathematics may offer a head start in data analytics, commerce students can absolutely transition into this field with the right training, skills development, and a passion for working with data.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Commerce students can pursue a career in data analytics. Data analytics is a field that involves the examination, cleansing, transformation, and interpretation of data to discover valuable insights and support decision-making. While a background in computer science or mathematics can be advantageous, it&#8217;s not a strict requirement for a career in data analytics. Here&#8217;s why &#8230; <a title=\"Can Commerce Student Do Data Analytics?\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/can-commerce-student-do-data-analytics\/\" aria-label=\"More on Can Commerce Student Do Data Analytics?\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":2788,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[224],"tags":[482],"class_list":["post-2786","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-question-answer","tag-can-commerce-student-do-data-analytics","generate-columns